profile_positions.description:
• Planned lessons on visual art and art history including architecture, landscape design, photography, drawing, painting, graphic design, story illustrations, and sculpture.
    • Used a variety of teaching methods and project-based learning techniques by incorporating new technologies and tools in the creative process, in order to create an enjoyable and productive classroom experience and develop lifelong skills;
    • Developed a syllabus to meet the needs, abilities, and interests of students;
    • Enabled students to create a functional portfolio of their artworks;
    • Planned, coordinated, and prepared art displays and exhibitions for the school and community;
    • Evaluated student achievements with formative and summative assessments, using an assessment framework related to specific knowledge and skills to acquire during every activity;
    • Communicated with staff and parents on student progress, attended department meetings and school meetings;
    • Met regularly with other departments to plan interdisciplinary projects.

In September 2021 I was assigned the role of coordinator of the art department for the implementation of the teaching curriculum and the supervision of the school art department. My duties:
    • Managed and chaired monthly department meetings, monitoring the art curriculum development in all grades;
    • Guaranteed a homogeneous pedagogical approach in the art department also developing new strategies where necessary;
    • Promoted and encouraged teachers to practice Project Based Learning in their classroom by proposing innovative activities and organizing an online art display to exhibit students’ work;
    • Managed the reorganization of the spaces and the redecoration of the new art lab.

• Delivered lectures on architectural building design, structural engineering, interior design, and landscape design;
    • Guided students through the understanding and management of project phases;
    • Taught the use of 2D and 3D Modelling software (Autocad, SketchUp, Revit);

• Involved with the maintenance, design, and development of the society properties.
    • Carried out all the building renovation projects and redecoration as well as the adaptation to the fire protection requirements and the accessibility requirements for persons with disabilities;
    • Managing the events promoted by the company such as meetings, conferences, and educational events;
    • Providing support to communication activities: promoting the events by producing advertisements, keeping updated web pages and other services on the hotel intranet;

• Managed interior design projects in cooperation with a team of 5 interior designers under the chief designer’s supervision, taking part in different interior design projects such as hotels, houses, restaurants, and stores located in Italy, France, and the United Arab Emirates.
    • Created design concepts including space planning, decorating plans furniture layouts, lighting, and color coordination;
    • Carried out all the interior design process, starting with the feasibility phase with sketches and mood boards and proceeding to all the steps from the concept and technical development to the construction phase.
    • Prepared 2D and 3D interior design presentations by using or hand drawings or computer-aided design software.
    • Participating in the negotiation process between the stakeholders (engineers, technical specialists, suppliers) and the chief architect discussing requirements, project solutions, schedule, procedures, and contracts;

• Managed small and large-scale projects in cooperation with a multi-disciplinary team under the chief architect’s supervision, for private clients and public institutions;
    • Carried out the architecture process, starting with the programming phase, and proceeding to all the steps from schematic design to the construction documents (site plan, demolitions plans, floor plans, elevations and sections, electrical drawings, and structural drawings).
    • Attended along with the chief architect and public institution regular meetings to discuss project requirements and changing needs.
